So chill and friendly here. My girlfriend and I arrived in Chicago pretty late so we had to find a place that had the kitchen open late. Luckily we just walked into here and their kitchen was still open at midnight. Our bartender was super nice, recommending places for us to go while we were in town. Drinks were really good and stiff. I recommend the old fashion if you are a whiskey drinker. The burger was great, and their grilled cheese has apples in it, which is unexpected, but was definitely a game changer. I recommend going here if you are looking for somewhere chill to drink/eat and listen to live music.

I really liked their dishes. I always get awesome service there. The place is well organised and the cashiers are always super friendly. Would recommend to others.

Beers on tap were good and prices in general were pretty fair for being downtown. The menu was varied though I ended up having a spicy chicken sandwich which I enjoyed and also shared an appetizer that was a bit more off the beaten track. I'd say all in all it's a place to go if you're a bit price sensitive but still want a bit more upscale feel downtown. The food will not blow you away, however, but it certainly is not bad.

The craft beers numbered over 50? The waiter who had our table was knowledgeable about both the food and beer choices. Dress was casual to formal. Pub is connected to the hotel Wit. Entrees start at about $30 for rather well prepared food. All of us were pretty impressed with the cooking. Entrees are well prepared and not jumbo portions. I did spy french fries at another table , but this isn't a french fries type of eatery. There were big screens on three walls but it was done in a tastefully subdued locations. Great for a date or family outing. I don't think it's a kids type resteraunt. Its a fun and trendy place . I was impressed .
Always stop in here when we are in Chicago for cocktails. Food is great too and the service is wonderful.

Popped in to pregame a show at the Chicago Theater due to proximity and couldn't be happier I did. The tavern is laid out and decorated beautifully. Plenty of seating at the bar. The bar tenders were quick and very attentive, very professional. It wasn't overly crowded but was starting to fill in as we were finishing up and they had no issue keeping up. Excellent beer selection both on draft and in bottles and cans. I appreciate the menu being segmented by style. Pricing was fair for being down town and not a complete arm and leg like I anticipated. Bonus points for a clean bathroom.

Guest at The Wit June 26 and 27, 2019.  Ate breakfast morning of June 27 at State and Lake.  I ordered a la carte due to dietary restrictions because nothing on their breakfast menu looked very appealing or seemed to be modifiable for my diet.  Coffee was horrible and cost $4.50.  I would have been better off walking a block down the street to the Starbucks.  I ordered a two egg omelette with cheddar cheese and a side of fruit.  Pretty sure that I was only given one egg, sort of scrambled, lukewarm with some cheese on top.  This cost $4.50.  Then, given a very tiny cup (not a cup really) of fruit that also cost $4.50.  Overpriced for a poorly cooked meal.  I did not order food at the hotel again for the rest of my stay.

This is a really great find in the Loop. I'm not sure whether the reason is that it's newer, or perhaps that is technically in a hotel, but it was not very crowded at noon on a weekday, when reservations at similar restaurants would be hard to find. Sorry I didn't enjoy this restaurant.  I asked for one of their menu cocktails to be made with gluten free vodka and was told they don't have any gluten free vodka which I find very hard to believe. It was happy hour and I ordered Chardonnay instead and got a short pour for $14. They had a limited food menu which lacked anything very healthy like salads??? I asked if this was their only food choices and was told that they're really just a bar.  My friend is vegetarian and I'm gluten free so we couldn't really see anything on the menu we wanted to eat.  Our waiter was not friendly once he knew we were not eating.  We were there before the 7:30pm Cher Show, which should have been a busy time, but not many people.  This is a great location, it should be booming, too bad. We ended up going to 312Chicago, and enjoyed a wonderful dinner before our show.
